    {
        "content": "<p>I think your definition makes sense. Another one would be: there exists a compact neighborhood <code>V</code> of the identity such that ..., but this one only makes sense in locally compact groups so your definition is better. It would be good to check that, in this case, the two definitions are equivalent, though.</p>",
